1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
And it's been a couple of weeks since we've been in the book of 2 Corinthians.

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:09,000
I preached the first few verses of this chapter a few weeks ago,

3
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:14,000
and then we had a group here from the Rapidan Baptist camp.

4
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:19,000
And then I preached a message from Acts 8, preached unto him Jesus.

5
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:23,000
And then now we're going to pick it back up here in 2 Corinthians 8.

6
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:26,000
As you know our theme, you see it on the banners behind me,

7
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:28,000
God's grace is sufficient.

8
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:32,000
And I'm so thankful for that biblical truth.

9
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:35,000
And each year, in fact on Thursday,

10
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:39,000
celebrated 14 years of being the pastor here at Fellowship Baptist Church.

11
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:43,000
And starting in 2012, I got here in August of 2011,

12
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:47,000
in 2012 we had a theme for that calendar year.

13
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:49,000
And every year we pick a theme,

14
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:54,000
and I preach something on Sunday mornings that goes along with that theme.

15
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:57,000
Often times it's been through a book of the Bible,

16
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:01,000
and sometimes there's been a few years where it's been a topical theme.

17
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:03,000
And this year, God's grace is sufficient.

18
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:06,000
I've been preaching on Sunday mornings through 2 Corinthians.

19
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:10,000
What a great book. We've learned many wonderful, valuable truths.

20
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:15,000
And we find here that as we enter into this section of the book of 2 Corinthians,

21
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:20,000
the Apostle Paul is dealing with a subject that sometimes people shy away from

22
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:26,000
because it's uncomfortable, but it's a biblical truth that God gives us,

23
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:29,000
and it's principles of giving.

24
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:32,000
And I'm thankful this morning that when we worship God,

25
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:35,000
there's a number of different ways in which we worship the Lord,

26
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:39,000
but one way that we worship God is through our giving.

27
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:42,000
And we see that throughout the entirety of Scripture.

28
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:45,000
In fact, in 2 Corinthians 9, I won't be dealing with it this morning,

29
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:49,000
but we find that the Bible says that God loveth a cheerful giver.

30
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:55,000
I find that one of the most exciting examples throughout all the Scripture

31
00:01:55,000 --> 00:02:02,000
of a cheerful giver is when David leads those to give towards the building of the temple.

32
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:08,000
He gave of his own resources. He then encourages others to give for the temple.

33
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:10,000
And they are rejoicing.

34
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:14,000
In fact, if you were to pick it up and look in the text of Scripture in 1 Chronicles,

35
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:20,000
and just kind of midpoint, you might think that they're rejoicing over some great military victory

36
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:22,000
or some other great feat,

37
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:26,000
but we find that the reason that they're rejoicing in the manner in which they are

38
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:29,000
is because God enabled them to give.

39
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:32,000
That they were able to give, and they were giving.

40
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:38,000
David was giving for the construction of a temple that he would never step foot in,

41
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:40,000
that he would never worship God in,

42
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:45,000
but he knew that God had enabled him to be able to give for a future generation.

43
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:49,000
And so I'm thankful that God gives us encouragement and truth.

44
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:54,000
In fact, as we look at the first six verses of this passage of Scripture a couple of weeks ago,

45
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:58,000
we dealt with verse number one, and notice the Bible says,

46
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:10,000
Now that would be Philippi, Thessalonica, Berea, Athens, Corinth.

47
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:15,000
Those were the places in which were going during that first missionary journey

48
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:18,000
that the Apostle Paul had the opportunity to go there to.

49
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:22,000
And those churches would be Philippi, Thessalonica, Berea.

50
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:28,000
And what an opportunity as Paul begins to encourage the believers in Corinth

51
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:33,000
with the testimony of those that he refers to as the churches of Macedonia.

52
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:37,000
Paul wanted them to know some things, and as we look through that text of Scripture,

53
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:41,000
we learn, first of all, that those believers were suffering.

54
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:45,000
The Bible describes their suffering as being deep poverty.

55
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:49,000
And as we notice that they're suffering, we also notice that they were surrendered.

56
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:55,000
The Bible tells us that they were first willing, they first gave their own selves to the Lord.

57
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:58,000
They were willing, in verse number three, of themselves.

58
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:00,000
And then we notice that they were sensitive.

59
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:03,000
They were sensitive to the leadership of the Holy Spirit of God in their lives.

60
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:05,000
We see that in verse one and verse five.

61
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:08,000
We see that they were sensitive to the needs of others.

62
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:13,000
And so as we look at that first six verses, again, it was a few weeks ago, just a quick recap,

63
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:17,000
we come to verse number seven, as we enter into our text this morning,

64
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:21,000
and notice what the Apostle Paul says as he's writing here to this church in Corinth.

65
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:26,000
He says, therefore, based upon what he's just mentioned and given,

66
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:32,000
he says, therefore, as ye abound in everything,

67
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:36,000
in faith, and utterance, and knowledge, and in all diligence,

68
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:43,000
and in your love to us, see that ye abound in this grace also.

69
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:49,000
I've titled the message from verse number seven, abound in this grace also.

70
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:52,000
I would say this morning that as we look at the text of Scripture,

71
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:56,000
and we'll make our way through verse number 15 as we get through it this morning,

72
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:59,000
but I would say that as we begin looking here at verse number seven,

73
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:03,000
and we see that the Apostle Paul says that ye abound in everything,

74
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:08,000
and he lists these things, but he says that ye abound in this grace also.

75
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:15,000
I'm reminded this morning that God has called his people to be complete in Christ.

76
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:19,000
God has called his people to be mature believers.

77
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:23,000
We're to grow in grace and knowledge of our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ

78
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:28,000
as we walk with Christ, and I don't know where you are on your journey,

79
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:32,000
but as we walk with him, and as we are conformed to the image of his dear son,

80
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:38,000
as we're growing and gaining that maturity where we are able to deal with

81
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:44,000
and to partake of that which God refers to as strong meat of the word,

82
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:48,000
we find that God wants us to be mature, to be complete.

83
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:50,000
I'm reminded, hold your place here in 2 Corinthians,

84
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:52,000
but turn to the book of 2 Peter if you will,

85
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:55,000
and we'll be back to 2 Corinthians 8 in just a moment,

86
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:59,000
but by way of introduction, I want to remind you of what Peter says

87
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:04,000
as he's writing here in 2 Peter chapter 1, and as he's writing to these believers,

88
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:12,000
we find that there's this obvious emphasis that is given with regard to growth spiritually,

89
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:17,000
and we understand the importance, we understand the growth charts

90
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:20,000
when we talk about physical growth, when we have children,

91
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:26,000
and you see their development and the different stages in which they go through,

92
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:33,000
and the reality is that as believers, there should be spiritual growth in your life and in my life,

93
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:36,000
and it should be that we're growing in grace and knowledge,

94
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:41,000
that we're not just kind of settled and getting stagnant and just kind of floundering around,

95
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:47,000
no, that we're going on unto perfection, that we're growing in our Christian life,

96
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:50,000
and here's what Peter says, here's how he says it in 2 Peter 1,

97
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:52,000
notice if you will, in verse number 3,

98
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:58,000
according as his divine power hath given unto us all things that pertain unto life and godliness,

99
00:06:58,000 --> 00:07:03,000
through the knowledge of him that hath called us to glory and virtue,

100
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:08,000
whereby are given unto us exceeding great and precious promises,

101
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:12,000
that by these ye might be partakers of the divine nature,

102
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:16,000
having escaped the corruption that is in the world through lust,

103
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:20,000
all that good stuff, verse 3 and 4, I mean, praise the Lord, I'm saved by the grace of God,

104
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:26,000
I understand that I have these precious promises, I understand the work that he's doing,

105
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:30,000
I've escaped the corruption that's in the world through lust, I mean, hallelujah,

106
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:35,000
but notice in verse number 5, and beside this, notice what he says,

107
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:42,000
giving all diligence, you ever see somebody that's not diligent?

108
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:46,000
You know what it is to be diligent, you know what it is to not be diligent,

109
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:55,000
and here Peter says giving all diligence, notice the next two words, add to, add to,

110
00:07:55,000 --> 00:08:02,000
now understand he's not saying that we add to so that we can be saved, stay saved, that we can know,

111
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:07,000
but we're to grow in our walk with Christ, we're to grow spiritually,

112
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:13,000
and he says add to your faith virtue, and to virtue knowledge,

113
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:18,000
and to knowledge temperance, and to temperance patience, and to patience godliness,

114
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:24,000
and to godliness brotherly kindness, and to brotherly kindness charity.

115
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:30,000
Now notice with me in verse number 8, he says for if, what does it say? These things.

116
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:37,000
He doesn't say if this thing, he says if these things, again, that's that growth,

117
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:45,000
spiritual growth in the life of a believer, if these things be in you and abound.

118
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:49,000
What did Paul say as we're looking at this passage in 2 Corinthians chapter 8?

119
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:52,000
Abound in this grace also.

120
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:58,000
And so Peter says that if these things be in you and abound,

121
00:08:58,000 --> 00:09:05,000
they make you that you shall neither be barren nor unfruitful in the knowledge of our Lord Jesus Christ.

122
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:10,000
See the reality is that as a believer, we want to abide in Christ,

123
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:15,000
we want to grow spiritually, we want to be fruitful in our Christian lives,

124
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:19,000
and we find that Peter says add these things, again,

125
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:23,000
we find that the product is that if they're in us and they abound,

126
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:29,000
they make you that you should neither be barren nor unfruitful in the knowledge of our Lord Jesus Christ.

127
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:35,000
I'm reminded of what the Lord Jesus Christ said to the scribes and Pharisees in Matthew 23 and verse 23.

128
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:38,000
You don't need to turn there, but here's what Jesus says.

129
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:40,000
Woe unto you.

130
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:43,000
Now anytime you see that phraseology, it'll caught your attention.

131
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:48,000
Why? Because Jesus is speaking, of course, he's talking to these scribes and Pharisees,

132
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:53,000
and notice what he says. Woe unto you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites.

133
00:09:53,000 --> 00:10:00,000
For ye pay tithe of mint and anise and cumin and have omitted the weightier matter.

134
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:05,000
matters of the law, judgment, mercy, and faith.

135
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:07,840
But then I want you to catch what Jesus says at the end.

136
00:10:07,840 --> 00:10:12,319
So he says, you're doing this, but you've omitted this.

137
00:10:12,319 --> 00:10:16,299
You're paying tithe of mint and anise and cumin,

138
00:10:16,299 --> 00:10:18,559
but you've omitted the weightier matters,

139
00:10:18,559 --> 00:10:21,200
the judgment, the mercy, and faith.

140
00:10:21,200 --> 00:10:26,200
And here's what Jesus says, these ought ye to have done

141
00:10:26,620 --> 00:10:29,940
and not to leave the other undone.

142
00:10:29,940 --> 00:10:31,360
So what's Jesus saying?

143
00:10:31,360 --> 00:10:34,720
You should be doing all of it, amen.

144
00:10:34,720 --> 00:10:38,939
Don't get this part right and not do this part.

145
00:10:38,939 --> 00:10:41,419
Don't do this part and not do this part.

146
00:10:41,419 --> 00:10:44,900
No, the complete in Christ.

147
00:10:44,900 --> 00:10:48,060
And we find that it's only through the work

148
00:10:48,060 --> 00:10:51,779
of the Holy Spirit, using the word of God,

149
00:10:51,779 --> 00:10:55,020
that God will allow us to be complete in him,

150
00:10:55,060 --> 00:10:58,020
that we can grow in knowledge of our Lord

151
00:10:58,020 --> 00:10:59,659
and Savior, Jesus Christ.

152
00:10:59,659 --> 00:11:03,580
Peter said, we read 2 Peter 1, but in 1 Peter 2,

153
00:11:03,580 --> 00:11:06,779
as newborn babes desire the sincere milk of the word,

154
00:11:06,779 --> 00:11:09,580
that ye may grow thereby.

155
00:11:09,580 --> 00:11:13,980
So now as Paul is referring to these here in Corinth,

156
00:11:13,980 --> 00:11:16,139
back in 2 Corinthians chapter number eight,

157
00:11:16,139 --> 00:11:19,080
we find that Paul offers praise to the churches

158
00:11:19,080 --> 00:11:22,660
of Macedonia for their sacrificial giving.

159
00:11:22,660 --> 00:11:26,379
He tells the church in Corinth that these churches

160
00:11:26,379 --> 00:11:29,660
of Macedonia, they gave sacrificially,

161
00:11:29,660 --> 00:11:32,739
they were an example, and now he's going

162
00:11:32,739 --> 00:11:34,940
to encourage the believers in Corinth

163
00:11:34,940 --> 00:11:39,900
to abound in this grace giving also.

164
00:11:39,900 --> 00:11:42,260
So notice in our text, if you're there back

165
00:11:42,260 --> 00:11:45,120
in 2 Corinthians chapter eight, in verse seven,

166
00:11:45,120 --> 00:11:47,660
and we'll see it in verse 10 and 11 as well,

167
00:11:47,660 --> 00:11:49,419
notice if you're taking notes, number one,

168
00:11:49,419 --> 00:11:52,500
Paul commends the believers in Corinth.

169
00:11:53,339 --> 00:11:54,940
Paul commends them.

170
00:11:54,940 --> 00:11:58,139
We find that he begins in verse number seven,

171
00:11:58,139 --> 00:12:03,139
he says, therefore, as ye abound in everything.

172
00:12:03,339 --> 00:12:05,839
And then Paul lists something specifically.

173
00:12:05,839 --> 00:12:10,100
He says, as he's commending these believers in Corinth,

174
00:12:10,100 --> 00:12:12,419
he references their faith.

175
00:12:13,259 --> 00:12:15,500
You know, this morning, it's important

176
00:12:15,500 --> 00:12:19,259
that we have the right belief, amen?

177
00:12:19,259 --> 00:12:22,660
It's important that we contend earnestly

178
00:12:22,660 --> 00:12:25,220
for the faith that was once delivered to the saints.

179
00:12:25,220 --> 00:12:28,339
It's important that we live by faith.

180
00:12:28,339 --> 00:12:30,899
We can use this word faith by understanding

181
00:12:30,899 --> 00:12:33,860
the body of doctrine that we hold to,

182
00:12:33,860 --> 00:12:36,020
but we also understand faith cometh by hearing,

183
00:12:36,020 --> 00:12:37,160
and hearing by the word of God.

184
00:12:37,160 --> 00:12:39,619
The just shall live by his faith,

185
00:12:39,619 --> 00:12:41,580
and we understand that without faith,

186
00:12:41,580 --> 00:12:43,100
it's impossible to please him,

187
00:12:43,100 --> 00:12:46,699
and Paul references their faith.

188
00:12:46,699 --> 00:12:48,779
Listen, it's important for us to know

189
00:12:49,179 --> 00:12:50,899
what the Bible teaches.

190
00:12:50,899 --> 00:12:53,500
It's important for us to be able to stand firm

191
00:12:53,500 --> 00:12:55,759
upon the truth of God's word.

192
00:12:55,759 --> 00:12:57,860
It's important that when somebody asks us

193
00:12:57,860 --> 00:12:59,460
of the hope that lieth within us,

194
00:12:59,460 --> 00:13:01,020
that we can go to the Bible,

195
00:13:01,020 --> 00:13:03,820
and we can take and prove biblically

196
00:13:03,820 --> 00:13:07,220
why we have the position that we do.

197
00:13:08,500 --> 00:13:12,020
So Paul, as he commends the believers in Corinth,

198
00:13:12,020 --> 00:13:13,300
he starts by their faith.

199
00:13:13,300 --> 00:13:18,300
He then says, and notice, in faith and utterance.

200
00:13:19,300 --> 00:13:21,820
Those are the things that we speak.

201
00:13:21,820 --> 00:13:23,660
And so Paul is acknowledging,

202
00:13:23,660 --> 00:13:25,580
now understand, there's a great difference

203
00:13:25,580 --> 00:13:26,899
between the church in Corinth

204
00:13:26,899 --> 00:13:28,940
in 1 Corinthians and 2 Corinthians.

205
00:13:28,940 --> 00:13:30,139
There's still some problems,

206
00:13:30,139 --> 00:13:33,740
but man, they responded to what Paul had written

207
00:13:33,740 --> 00:13:35,979
to them in 1 Corinthians,

208
00:13:35,979 --> 00:13:38,660
and there's some growth that's obvious

209
00:13:38,660 --> 00:13:41,699
when you read 1 Corinthians and 2 Corinthians.

210
00:13:41,699 --> 00:13:43,979
There's some growth that has taken place

211
00:13:43,979 --> 00:13:47,020
within the believers in Corinth.

212
00:13:47,020 --> 00:13:49,179
And so Paul says, I'm commending you.

213
00:13:49,179 --> 00:13:50,020
Why?

214
00:13:50,020 --> 00:13:53,380
Because you abound in everything in faith and utterance.

215
00:13:53,380 --> 00:13:56,220
And then he says, he references their knowledge.

216
00:13:56,220 --> 00:13:57,820
He says, and knowledge.

217
00:13:57,820 --> 00:14:01,220
Now, when we look at the biblical word for knowledge here,

218
00:14:01,220 --> 00:14:03,139
and understand what Paul's talking about,

219
00:14:03,139 --> 00:14:05,820
he's really referencing not just the knowledge

220
00:14:05,820 --> 00:14:09,100
of worldly wisdom or worldly things.

221
00:14:09,100 --> 00:14:11,300
No, he's talking about the knowledge of God.

222
00:14:12,460 --> 00:14:13,820
How do we know God?

223
00:14:14,820 --> 00:14:16,500
We only know God through his word.

224
00:14:17,660 --> 00:14:20,059
To know God is to know his word.

225
00:14:20,059 --> 00:14:23,380
And you can ask people questions about who is God

226
00:14:23,380 --> 00:14:25,579
and what their thoughts are about God,

227
00:14:25,579 --> 00:14:28,540
and they could give you a number of different answers

228
00:14:28,540 --> 00:14:30,420
based on various sources,

229
00:14:30,420 --> 00:14:35,220
but I'm thankful this morning that God gave us a Bible.

230
00:14:35,220 --> 00:14:38,339
And that in the Bible, he's revealed himself to us,

231
00:14:38,339 --> 00:14:40,540
and he wants us to know who he is.

232
00:14:40,540 --> 00:14:43,019
He wants us to know that he loves us,

233
00:14:43,179 --> 00:14:46,260
that he wants us to know the plan of redemption,

234
00:14:46,260 --> 00:14:48,779
of salvation through the Lord Jesus Christ

235
00:14:48,779 --> 00:14:50,739
as we study the scriptures.

